text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia crassicarpa (northern wattle, thick-podded salwood, brown salwood, Papua New Guinea red wattle, red wattle; syn. Racosperma crassicarpum (A.Cunn. ex Benth.) Pedley.) is a tree native to Australia (Queensland), West Papua (Indonesia) and Papua New Guinea.
